1) Arduino IDE: File > Preferences > Additional Boards Manager URL

2) Add the URL of the ESP32 manufacturers driver to the URL field. 
   https://dl.espressif.com/dl/package_esp32_index.json

3) Go to: Tools > Board > Boards Manager

4) In the search field enter: "esp32"
   Look for and click on "esp32 Espressif Systems driver". 
   Click the install button.

5) Go to: File > Examples
   Load one of the ESP32 sketches to get started. 
